==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Meagre
<hw>Mea"gre</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>merge</ets>, F. <ets>maigre</ets>, L.
<ets>macer</ets>; akin to D. & G. <ets>mager</ets>, Icel.
<ets>magr</ets>, and prob. to Gr. <grk>makro`s</grk> long. Cf.
<er>Emaciate</er>, <er>Maigre</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of, or having little, flesh;
lean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Meager</qex> were his looks;⟦br⟧
Sharp misery had worn him to the bones.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute of richness, fertility, strength, or the
like; defective in quantity, or poor in quality; poor; barren; scanty in
ideas; wanting strength of diction or affluence of imagery; <as>as,
<ex>meager</ex> resources; <ex>meager</ex> fare</as>. Opposite of
<ant>ample</ant>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns> [Narrower terms:
<stype>exiguous</stype>] [Narrower terms: <stype>hardscrabble,
marginal</stype>] [Narrower terms: <stype>measly, miserable,
paltry</stype>] ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Meager</xex> soil.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> meagre, meagerly, scanty.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of secular habits and <qex>meager</qex> religious belief.</q>
<rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His education had been but <qex>meager</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Motley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Dry and harsh to the touch, as
chalk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>less than a desirable amount; -- of items
distributed from a larger supply.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> scrimpy, skimpy, skimping.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Thin; lean; lank; gaunt; starved; hungry; poor;
emaciated; scanty; barren.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meagre</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Meager</ent>⟦br⟧
